    CondCmsnSubPlan Represents a conditional sub-plan. A conditional sub-plan's conditions must be satisfied by a policy in order to apply.

    • Method Detail

      • getRenewalRange

        com.guidewire.bc.domain.commission.impl.RenewalRange getRenewalRange(int startRenewal,
                                                                   int endRenewal)
        Returns a utility object for getting and setting the availability of this sub-plan for a given renewal range. A renewal range is used to filter policies by checking the policy TermNumber. A policy with the TermNumber 1 has been renewed 0 times, a policy with the TermNumber 2 has been renewed 1 time and so on. The range has an inclusive lower bound and an exclusive lower bound so a policy is within a range if start <= (TermNumber - 1) < end
        Parameters:
        startRenewal - the start of the renewal range, inclusive
        endRenewal - the end of the renewal range, exclusive. A value of -1 means the range is unbounded
        Returns:
        a newly created range object. Always returns a new object even if the range bounds don't make sense; the bounds will be checked when the range is actually used to check or update the sub-plan

      • getRenewalRangeOnOrAfter

        com.guidewire.bc.domain.commission.impl.RenewalRange getRenewalRangeOnOrAfter(int startRenewal)
        Returns a utility object for getting and setting the availability of this sub-plan for a given renewal range. Constructs a range that starts at the given value but is unbounded on the upper end
        Parameters:
        startRenewal - the start of the renewal range, inclusive
        Returns:
        a newly created range object. Always returns a new object even if the start of the range doesn't make sense; the range bounds are checked when the range is actually used to check or update the sub-plan

      • changePriority

        void changePriority(int delta)
        Changes the priority of this sub-plan by the given delta. Implicitly alters the priority of all intervening sub-plans - so if this sub-plan was currently 2 then a delta of -1 would change this plan's priority to 1, while the sub-plan that was previously 1 would be given the priority 2.
        Parameters:
        delta - amount to increase or decrease the priority of the sub-plan. Lower priorities are higher so a negative delta increases the priority of the sub-plan
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the magnitude of delta is so big that the sub-plan cannot be given a matching priority
